From 871575936c176cdbc33f78cf0f5622d353db32d7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <fix@alaruel>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 18:13:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix asset assignment gap: create map form, image rendering,
 NPC portrait picker

- Make maps.image_asset_id nullable (was NOT NULL) so maps can be
  created without an image assigned upfront
- Add Create Map modal in AtlasView with name, optional asset picker
  (populated from maps-category assets), canvas dimensions, and scale
- Add + button in sidebar Maps section as second entry point to create
- Render actual map image in SVG canvas via assets:resolve IPC bridge;
  falls back to grid pattern with hint text when no image assigned
- Auto-fill canvas dimensions from selected asset's stored width/height
- Add portrait asset picker to NpcDetail edit form (portraits category)
- Add portrait asset picker to NpcCreateModal
- Display resolved portrait image in NPC detail header avatar
- All asset pickers show a hint when no assets of that category exist yet
